data.content:
**In .NET 11, all four methods in your repository will throw at runtime.** The Cosmos DB provider's sync-over-async opt-in has been **fully removed** — there is no way to re-enable it.

Every synchronous LINQ operator (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` now unconditionally throws against the Cosmos provider.

**Fix:** Convert to async equivalents:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through your callers — every call site must `await` these methods and become `async` itself. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
